div.div:
This diagram shows network traffic for a single ECS cluster in one AZ. It has two subnets, a public one that routes traffic directly to the Internet and a private one that routes through a NAT gateway.
The subnets, EC2 instances, and NAT gateway will be replicated to a second AZ. (The ALB sort of spans the AZs.)
We plan to deploy 2 separate ECS clusters, one for production traffic and one for staging instances. These will share a VPC but have separate subnet stacks. The staging cluster will only be in one AZ.
Arrows show the direction of the request. Response data is implied. Container requests are sparse for clarity; any container may actually make any of the requests shown.
